HEADWORD: Kohnur
<hw>Koh`*nur</hw> }</mhw>
<pr>(k⟦omac⟧`⟦icr⟧*n⟦oomac⟧r")</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Per.
<ets>koh-i-n⟦umac⟧r</ets>, lit., mountain of light.]</ety> <def>A famous
diamond, surrendered to the British crown on the annexation of the
Punjab. According to Hindu legends, it was found in a Golconda mine, and
has been the property of various Hindu and Persian rulers.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

